# Real-Time Multiplayer Arena System

## Quick Overview

This project now includes a complete real-time multiplayer battle system using Firebase.

## Files Created

### Core System
- `src/types/battle-room.ts` - TypeScript type definitions
- `src/hooks/useRealtimeArena.ts` - Main React hook (600+ lines)
- `src/components/arena/RealtimeBattleRoom.tsx` - Full UI component

### Firebase Functions
- `functions/src/index.ts` - Matchmaker + cleanup functions
- `functions/package.json` - Dependencies
- `functions/tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config
- `functions/.gitignore` - Git ignore rules

### Documentation
- `REALTIME_ARENA_GUIDE.md` - Comprehensive guide (500+ lines)
- `REALTIME_ARENA_SETUP.md` - Setup instructions
- `REALTIME_ARENA_QUICKREF.md` - Quick reference
- `REALTIME_ARENA_IMPLEMENTATION_COMPLETE.md` - Implementation summary
- `functions/README.md` - Functions documentation

## Key Features

✅ Real-time sync via Firebase onSnapshot
✅ Room code system (6-char codes like "ABC123")
✅ Automatic matchmaking
✅ Turn-based state machine
✅ Heartbeat connection monitoring
✅ Animation system
✅ Full TypeScript support

## Usage

```typescript
import { useRealtimeArena } from '@/hooks/useRealtimeArena';

const { room, createRoom, joinRoom, playAction } = useRealtimeArena();
```

## Deploy

```bash
cd functions
npm install
npm run build
firebase deploy --only functions
```

## Test

1. Open two browser windows
2. Window 1: Create room, note code
3. Window 2: Join with code
4. Both: Submit actions
5. Watch real-time sync!

---

All requirements met ✅
